%%{init: {'theme': 'dark', 'sequence': {'mirrorActors': false, 'messageAlign': 'center'}}}%%

sequenceDiagram
    participant W1 as Worker 1
    participant W2 as Worker 2
    participant EC as Execution<br/>Coordinator
    participant MC as Monitoring<br/>Coordinator
    participant CPU as CPU Monitor<br/>(JMX)
    participant MEM as Memory Monitor<br/>(JMX)
    participant CP as Control Plane<br/>Thread

    Note over W1,CP: 🟢 NORMAL OPERATION — Zero monitoring threads running

    Note over W1: processChunk(tenants 1-50)
    W1->>EC: pauseIfAnyMonitorHot()
    activate EC
    EC->>MC: sampleMonitors()
    activate MC
    Note over MC: synchronized + 100ms debounce
    MC->>CPU: evaluate()
    CPU-->>MC: NORMAL (45%)
    MC->>MEM: evaluate()
    MEM-->>MC: NORMAL (52%)
    MC-->>EC: all NORMAL
    deactivate MC
    EC-->>W1: continue
    deactivate EC
    Note over W1: processChunk(tenants 51-100)

    Note over W1,CP: 🔴 PRODUCTION TRAFFIC SPIKE — CPU rises

    W1->>EC: pauseIfAnyMonitorHot()
    activate EC
    EC->>MC: sampleMonitors()
    activate MC
    MC->>CPU: evaluate()
    CPU-->>MC: 🔥 HOT (85%)
    Note over MC: Short-circuit: skip remaining monitors
    MC-->>EC: HOT detected!
    deactivate MC

    rect rgb(183, 28, 28)
        Note over W1,CP: ⏸ PAUSE TRIGGERED
        EC->>W1: signal pause
        EC->>W2: signal pause (interrupt if idle)
        EC->>CP: start resume polling
    end
    deactivate EC

    Note over W1: awaitResume() — blocked
    Note over W2: awaitResume() — blocked
    Note over W1,W2: Workers consume ZERO CPU while paused

    loop Every 5 seconds (only while paused)
        CP->>MC: sampleMonitors()
        MC->>CPU: evaluate()
        CPU-->>MC: HOT (78%)
        MC->>MEM: evaluate()
        MEM-->>MC: NORMAL (55%)
        MC-->>CP: still HOT
    end

    CP->>MC: sampleMonitors()
    MC->>CPU: evaluate()
    CPU-->>MC: NORMAL (45%) ✅
    MC->>MEM: evaluate()
    MEM-->>MC: NORMAL (48%) ✅
    MC-->>CP: all NORMAL

    rect rgb(27, 94, 32)
        Note over W1,CP: ▶ RESUME TRIGGERED
        CP->>EC: executeResume()
        EC->>W1: wake up
        EC->>W2: wake up
    end

    Note over W1,CP: 🟢 NORMAL OPERATION RESUMES
    W1->>EC: processChunk(tenants 101-150)
    W2->>EC: processChunk(next task chunk)
